{"id":558,"date":"2017-03-10T20:55:03","date_gmt":"2017-03-10T20:55:03","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/?p=558"},"modified":"2022-01-18T11:51:42","modified_gmt":"2022-01-18T11:51:42","slug":"translating-ticket-priorities-and-ticket-statuses","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/translating-ticket-priorities-and-ticket-statuses\/","title":{"rendered":"Translating ticket priorities and ticket statuses"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Ticket priorities and ticket statuses are stored in the database, however, with Perfex CRM you have the ability to translate them based on their ID.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note that changing the name from the admin area won&#8217;t<\/strong> affect how will be shown to the customers\/staff members, you will need to change\/include it in the language file by creating your own custom_lang.php file. The names from the admin area are used for\u00a0your own recognition.<br><br>Only statuses\/priorities\u00a0that don&#8217;t exist<strong> in the language files will be shown the same like they are in the database.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Translating ticket statuses<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>By default all the predefined system statuses will be included in the language files with the following keys:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>ticket_status_db_1 (Open)<\/li><li>ticket_status_db_2 (In Progress)<\/li><li>ticket_status_db_3 (Answered)<\/li><li>ticket_status_db_4 (On Hold)<\/li><li>ticket_status_db_5 (Closed)<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If we want to&nbsp;translate&nbsp;the ticket status <strong>Open, <\/strong>this status is with ID&nbsp;1 create your own <a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/overwrite-translation-text\/\">custom_lang.php<\/a> file and add the following lang key:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>$lang&#91;'ticket_status_db_1'] = 'My Open Ticket Status';<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Translating ticket priorities<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>By default all the predefined system priorities&nbsp;will be included in the language files with the following keys:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>ticket_priority_db_1 (Low)<\/li><li>ticket_priority_db_2&nbsp;(Medium)<\/li><li>ticket_priority_db_3&nbsp;(High)<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If we want to&nbsp;translate&nbsp;the ticket status <strong>Low, this priority&nbsp;is with ID&nbsp;1 create your own <a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/overwrite-translation-text\/\">custom_lang.php<\/a> file and add the following lang key:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>$lang&#91;'ticket_priority_db_1'] = 'Low Priority';<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p>If you add your own&nbsp;status\/priority you can find id on the left side of the table the first column will be ID.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"459\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/trans-ticket-status-id-768x459.png\" alt=\"translating tickets\" class=\"wp-image-559\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/trans-ticket-status-id-768x459.png 768w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/trans-ticket-status-id-768x459-300x179.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/trans-ticket-status-id-768x459-60x36.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/trans-ticket-status-id-768x459-150x90.png 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Translating new ticket status<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"324\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/trans-2new-ticket-status-translate-768x324.png\" alt=\"translating new ticket status\" class=\"wp-image-560\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/trans-2new-ticket-status-translate-768x324.png 768w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/trans-2new-ticket-status-translate-768x324-300x127.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/trans-2new-ticket-status-translate-768x324-60x25.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/trans-2new-ticket-status-translate-768x324-150x63.png 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>On the screenshot, there is new ticket status created Work Done with ID 6.<\/p>\n\n\n<p>If you don&#8217;t add this ticket status in your custom_lang.php by default will be shown as Work Done.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To translate the ticket status navigate to your <a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/overwrite-translation-text\/\">custom_lang.php<\/a> file and add the following line:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>$lang&#91;'ticket_priority_db_6'] = 'Work Done';<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see the language key is ending with the status ID (_6).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The same process is with the ticket priorities.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Ticket priorities and ticket statuses are stored in the database, however, with Perfex CRM you have the ability to translate them based on their ID. Note that changing the name from the admin area won&#8217;t affect how will be shown to the customers\/staff members, you will need to change\/include it in the language file by [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[12],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-558","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-support-tickets"],"aioseo_notices":[],"